uction of property.<br><br>Have you ever put a DVD into a CD player only to get funky readouts and an eject...THIS is what happens when a company makes a product that is not compatible with hardware, NOT a destruction of the equipment.<br><br>Even if a warning is labeled (which the original poster said it was not at the time of HIS purchase), its still illegal...damn, tobbacco has been sued and lost hundreds of times despite warnings on every carton/pack/damn near cigarette themselves (I think thats rediculous BTW).<br><br>Regardless of all this, if a company wants to limit my ability to use their product in the interest of preventing theft, and use means to destroy my equipment in this interest, I WILL turn to stealing their product in one way or another. The masses will always be able to get around security, we always have...dont piss the ones who DO support you off. <p>Hutterr Verbruggen55 DroodFallen shadows</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udovelyngoldenheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dovelyn Goldenheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 445<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/6/02 12:15:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=720.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Copy Protections</span><hr size=1> I honestly don't think they should copy protect them anyway.  I make copies of my own CD's for pesonal use all the time.  I'd much rather carry around a copy in my car than the original.  Can't find the case? Screw it, through it in the glove compartment.  Gets stolen?  Who cares.  I also used to make copies of my records and tapes.  I think the industry is getting a little out of hand here.  I agree with whoever said, screw it, I'll just download it instead if they are going to penalize those of us who actually do buy CD's. <p><p align="left"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26803"><img src="http://home.austin.rr.com/fianna/DoveSig.jpg" border="0"></a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udovelyngoldenheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dovelyn Goldenheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 446<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/6/02 12:17:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=720.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Copy Protections</span><hr size=1> through it in the glove compartment = throw it in the glove compartment (stupid no edit button!)<br><br>Also, I forgot to add, how many people don't make &quot;mix&quot; CD's of their own, legally purchased music?  I do, and I resent them forcing me to illegally download it in order to be able to make a CD with the songs I want. <p><p align="left"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26803"><img src="http://home.austin.rr.com/fianna/DoveSig.jpg" border="0"></a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugaludina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galudina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/6/02 1:14:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=720.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fatcatdesign.org.uk/galudinasigside.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Copy Protections</span><hr size=1> Not sure how this compares in the US but here in the UK you would be able to take legal action against both the shop you bought the CD from and the company making the CD (manufacturer and distributer)<br><br>Its simply not good enough that warning stickers are placed on CD's, there was no warning sticker on your CD and the replacement of your drive is the responsibility of firstly the shop (for its the shop you have a contact of sale with - Sale of Goods Act here not sure in US) but also the manufacturer.<br><br>I wouldn't let this go and would be demanding a new drive and damages for the hassle, but then thats me  <br><br>I haven't come across this in the UK yet but I feel they are walking a litigation tightrope even with the stickers.<br><br>If you can start with the store manager, make your complaint IN the store nice and public but pleasant but firm and LOUD lol If not able to do this or it dosen't get you action then complain by letter (keeping copies) and send duplicates to any consumer rights places you can find, CO's of the company etc  <br><br>Good luck<br><br>Galudina  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usorataarisugawas4h.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sorata  Arisugawa S4H</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/6/02 10:09:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=720.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Copy Protections</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> So bought a new CD yesterday. (Yes, bought, because i believed in supporting the artists.) <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>My opinion is that the second they stop making making music for the music, then that is the moment they are no longer an artist.<br><br>The Dave Mathews Band is one of the few bands out there that I believe still make music becuase they like to make music, not for the money.  I admit it has been a while since I have been to a concert so I may be a bit out of date on things.  But when I went to a DMB concert, I was amazed at the number of recorders I saw.  DMB is one of the few bands that allow people to record their music at their concerts, which gave me a greater respect for them.<br><br>------------------------------------------------<br><br>As for making CDs that won't work in CD-ROM/DVD drives...<br><br>I say they can go screw themselves.  First off, it is no longer about making music anymore, it's about profits.  Second, there is nothing morally wrong with ripping MP3s from a CD (as long as it's your CD and you're making the MP3 for yourself only).  Third, more and more CD players are becoming more like CD-Rom drives.  I wonder how many car CD players may get dammaged from those types of CDs.<br><br>They are shooting themselves in the foot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uelysianaheathertoes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ElysianaHeathertoes</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/6/02 4:13:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=720.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Copy Protections</span><hr size=1> I also make a lot of CDs of my own music for use in my car. Go buy a 2 CD GH collection? Put em on 1 CD and ride. It occurs to me the music industry has no right to affect the consumer's fair-use. If a drive says CD, ALL CDs should be playable on it. And for that to not be the case, is dubious.<br><br>I agree. What has been done here is illegal, and needs to be exposed. I can imagine this kind of thing would get national exposure, not to mention the face that these people would be in some big trouble with the law. Some people just can't get it through their heads that you don't shi't on your customers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showMessageRange?topicID=720.topic&start=21&stop=28>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showPrevMessage?topicID=720.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showNextMessage?topicID=720.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=720.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.emailToFriend?topicID=720.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.threadControl?topicID=720.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.subscribeUnregisteredToTo